  "text": "In 2017, Price et al. [CITATION_1] quantified the spectral, angular and dynamic performance of 11 actigraph models from eight manufacturers or research groups, including the Daysimeter and new Actiwatch Spectrum models. Price and Lyachev 66 also described a subsequent modification to the ActTrust device (Condor Instruments, Sao Paulo, Brazil), which is designed to match the spectral response of melanopsin. As noted earlier, the spectral sensitivity of the human circadian system is not limited to the melanopsin response only, so the usability of such devices for circadian research may still be limited.",
